<subSubSection id="BF0A547B89584D54A35735EF5D4CCDC7" pageId="0" pageNumber="201" type="notes">
<paragraph id="373D27AEAB76DD31AA93D6B70C16E906" pageId="0" pageNumber="201">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7022C794C6EBE4B3CF03B2F4813E77B5" pageId="0" pageNumber="201">
This species was recorded by 
<bibRefCitation id="53869EE2A65A72A83086179CD07C107B" author="Erlandsson, S" journalOrPublisher="Eos Madrid" pageId="0" pageNumber="201" pagination="11 - 93" refId="B6" refString="Erlandsson, S, 1972. Hymenoptera Aculeata from the European parts of the Mediterranean Countries. Eos Madrid 48: 11 - 93" title="Hymenoptera Aculeata from the European parts of the Mediterranean Countries." volume="48" year="1972">Erlandsson (1972)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="6F37D51B06ACD4B3DE956BCF11F1B3F7" author="Schembri, SP" journalOrPublisher="Bollettino della Societa' Entomologica Italiana" pageId="0" pageNumber="201" pagination="90 - 93" refId="B16" refString="Schembri, SP, 1980. Vespoidea from the Maltese Islands (Hymenoptera Aculeata). Bollettino della Societa' Entomologica Italiana 112 (4-6): 90 - 93" title="Vespoidea from the Maltese Islands (Hymenoptera Aculeata)." volume="112" year="1980">Schembri (1980)</bibRefCitation>
. Its distribution range includes Sicily, Malta and Southeast Europe (including Rhodes); it is also found in Cyprus and the Middle East. Individuals of this species may vary somewhat in tergite morphology (
<bibRefCitation id="E90DA7CD50305AC82EF65C7A3F22E418" author="Gusenleitner, J" journalOrPublisher="Eos Madrid" pageId="0" pageNumber="201" refId="B12" refString="Gusenleitner, J, 1998b. Vespoidea und Sapygidae gesammelt auf der Insel Samos (Hymenoptera: Eumenidae, Masaridae, Sapygidae). Linzer Biologische Beitraege 30/1: 155-161." title="Vespoidea und Sapygidae gesammelt auf der Insel Samos (Hymenoptera: Eumenidae, Masaridae, Sapygidae). Linzer Biologische Beitraege 30 / 1: 155 - 161." year="1998 b">Gusenleitner 1998b</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
